Liquidity allows me to be fluid and easily transition between these two platforms. Again, this is my form of risk management. 

What is the percentage of ETH to NFT ratio in your wallet? Iâ€™m curious â€“ let me know! 
#NFTs #web3

3. When Crypto market goes up, NFT market goes down ğŸ“ˆ
This ties in with point 2 above. When the crypto/altcoin market is down, I would allocate some of my liquid ETHs to buy into these dips. When the NFT market goes down, I take profits from my altcoin gains and put it into NFT
Obviously, how much liquidity you want to have is dependent on your risk tolerance, but holding ETH reduces anxiety and prevents panic selling.

For example, you invested 100% of your ETH into NFTs and the market declines by 20%. Your entire unrealized loss will be at 20%. If you invested 80% into NFTs and 20% held in ETH, a market decline of 20% will result in the same unrealized loss of 16%.

2.Reducing volatility in your NFT portfolio ğŸ’¹
Holding ETH may reduce returns when the NFT market is pumping, but in general, it can act as an anchor within your portfolio to mitigate losses as your entire portfolio declines (which it will at some point).
If you are in a liquidity crunch, youâ€™ll have to try and sell one of your NFTs asap to get liquidityâ€¦and we know that sometimes, certain JPEGs just donâ€™t sell. You snooze, you lose.

1.Liquidity provides opportunity. ğŸ¤‘

A key advantage of holding ETH is that it allows for opportunistic purchases when floor prices drop on a project that Iâ€™ve been eyeing for a while or if I want to ride a wave on a project thatâ€™s pumping in volume.
